modules.description: Provides operations to construct and manipulate benchmark trees, including naming nodes with `@>`, prefixing subtrees with `@>>`, merging trees with `concat`, and filtering paths with `filter`. Works with `t` (benchmark trees), `path` (string lists), and `arg_state` (command-line parsing state). Used to build hierarchical benchmarks, filter execution paths, and integrate with command-line arguments for selective benchmark runs.

Measures and compares the execution time of OCaml functions, supporting both single and repeated runs. It works with function values and timing statistics, returning results in structured formats. Used to evaluate performance differences between implementations of algorithms.

Provides operations to construct, manipulate, and filter benchmark trees, enabling hierarchical structuring, path-based selection, and command-line integration. Supports types `t` (benchmark trees), `path` (string lists), and `arg_state` (command-line parsing state), with operations like `@>`, `@>>`, `concat`, and `filter`. Example: build a tree with named nodes, filter specific paths for execution, or merge multiple benchmarks into a single structure. Can be used to organize complex benchmark suites, selectively run subsets of tests, or combine results from different execution paths.
